message.content:
You are 21.

Explanation:
- You said you are not a prime number, so you must be an integer greater than 1 that has factors other than 1 and itself.
- You said you are between 20 and 40, so your possible values are 21, 22, 23, ..., 39.
- You said you are one more than a square number, so you must be the next integer after a perfect square. The perfect squares between 20 and 40 are 20, 25, and 36. Since you are not 20 or 36, you must be 21, which is one more than the square of 4.

Therefore, you are 21.
